gomodel:SYNGO_5534  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" , "Rationale: Figure 3, S6d: \"To identify AP-3-dependent cargo more comprehensively, we used mass spectrometry (MS) with isotopic labeling by tandem mass tags (TMTs) to compare the protein composition of SVs from WT and mocha mice (Supplementary Table 1). ... However, the biggest reduction other than the AP-3 subunits themselves involved the phospholipid flippase ATP8A1, followed closely by its auxiliary subunit TMEM30A (CDC50a)\"\n\nFigure 4: Loss of AP-3 redistributes ATP8A1 away from SVs.\n\nFigure 5: Loss of ATP8A1 impairs release at high frequency.\n\nFigure 6: Loss of ATP8A1 reduces the SV association of synapsin.\n\nFigure 7: Interaction with synapsin mediates the function of ATP8A1 in transmitter release.. Experimental description: \"Atp8a1 knockout (strain no. 006433), Vamp2 knockout (strain no. 006380) and Syt1 knockout (strain no. 002478) mice were obtained from The Jackson Laboratory.\"\n\nantibody;\nATP8A1 rabbit polyclonal (1:300 dilution, catalog no. 21565-1-AP) from Proteintech" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5534" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

